			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-3618691">
									

<p>It was a good choice to tone down the 'corruption' somewhat to make it more legible, but I think it blows that you felt pressured into posting as a tale, because I think it hits on enough format-points to sit comfortably in a mainlist spot.</p>
<p>I do miss the Peppa Pig bits - they were quite unsettling. I personally feel that a better choice would have been to weave that element throughout the article in some fashion to maintain cohesiveness, but I imagine it was far simpler to scrap it entirely.</p>
<hr />
<p>To those who feel this works better as a Tale, I do wonder why? Could anyone elaborate on that other than simply saying it is as if that should be self-evident? It has all the basic formatting elements, albeit with gross deviations due to interference&#8230;so I'm not sure why it wouldn't belong other than 'it's better this way'.</p>

							</div>

								
					
