														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-3618702">
									

<p>Unlike stuff like <a href="/scp-2710">SCP-2710</a> (which has warmed on me over the years), which features back-and-forth discussion happening directly in the SCP document itself, your 001 proposal which is built around prose, or <a href="/scp-3999">SCP-3999</a> where reality is breaking down both in the document itself and with the document itself reflecting reality breaking down, this tale just has the standard SCP stuff with corruption in it before it takes an immediate hard-right turn into actual prose. So for readers it can be very jarring for this to be a mainlist SCP. I list those three SCPs because I feel they are the closest to what this SCP represents in terms of style, but it doesn't really approach why any of those three SCPs work the way they work.</p>
<p>Now, granted, I actually would not be opposed to this being in the mainlist and I'd still upvote it, but I think it's just gonna be received better as a tale. 3999 would not work as a tale, your proposal would not work as a tale, 2710 would not work as a tale. This however is on the fence and can go either way, but it fits much better as a tale than an SCP on the whole.</p>

							</div>

								
					
