														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-3619173">
									

<p>+1</p>
<p>When beginners write skips, I often tell them that they need a hook: an emotional connection, an interesting creepy effect, or a little mystery for the reader to solve. All of your works, author, seem to nail all three of those examples, and I think this piece is a really great example.</p>
<p>I do wish you had posted this as a mainlist skip, because I would like to see it &quot;canonized,&quot; so to speak, and because I think it is an excellent example of an infohazards, and just how horrifying an infohazard can be.</p>
<p>(Also, was General Electric a reference to Ophites skips?)</p>

							</div>

								
					
