														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-3619235">
									

<p>I remember reading the previous versions of this &#8212; well, skimming, admittedly &#8212; and liking the kind of imagery that was being created, but found the format screw way too frustrating to parse out. You've toned that down enough that the reader doesn't have to slog through incomprehensible hooplah to get to the meat, and a balance has been struck where the corruption seasons the meat instead of eating away at it, I think</p>
<p>I'm awful at reading into subtext, though, so there's probably a complete story with all threads resolved that I'm just too dense to clue into</p>
<blockquote>
<p><span style="color:white">I assume LaFerrier either created an anomaly to bring his son back to life, or created the anomaly as an embodiment of his grief, or the anomaly is his son, or something???</span></p>
</blockquote>

